"{\"uid\": \"www.tribune242.com.-news-2016-jun-27-brexit-creates-trading-nightmare-caribbean--Part2\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"investment that now exists.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 27, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Importantly, it should be recognised that the EU-EPA is the only such formal comprehensive arrangement that Caribbean countries have with any other country or region of the world.\", \"from\": 29, \"to\": 208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is vital to maintain as much of it as possible.\", \"from\": 209, \"to\": 259, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There had been some speculation in Britain during the 'Brexit' debate that Britain could resuscitate trade among the 52 other Commonwealth countries.\", \"from\": 261, \"to\": 410, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But, that idea, rooted in Empire, is not only impractical, it would not reap for Britain the trade rewards it derives from the EU.\", \"from\": 411, \"to\": 541, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Britain's earnings from exports to the Commonwealth, is not huge, representing only 9.76 per cent of its total exports in 2014, while its merchandise exports to the EU represented a hefty 45 per cent of its total exports.\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In any event, total Commonwealth trade in goods has declined over the years.\", \"from\": 765, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And, even its share of world trade is owed to the trading capacity of only six of the Commonwealth states - Singapore, India, Malaysia, Australia, Britain and Canada.\", \"from\": 842, \"to\": 1008, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Moreover, that trade is not between themselves.\", \"from\": 1009, \"to\": 1056, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For instance, China is Australia's biggest trading partner, and the US and Mexico are Canada's.\", \"from\": 1057, \"to\": 1152, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 2014, the six countries accounted for 84 per cent of all Commonwealth exports; 47 countries combined, including South Africa and Nigeria made up only 16 per cent.\", \"from\": 1153, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not surprisingly, the 36 Commonwealth small states, including the 12 in the Caribbean, enjoy only a tiny share of Commonwealth exports.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1454, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As for the notion that Commonwealth countries could fashion a Commonwealth Free Trade Agreement (FTA) under which they could give preferences to each other to expand intra-Commonwealth trade, while this is technically possible to make it compliant with World Trade Organisation rules, it is enormously difficult from a legal, administrative and even political standpoint.\", \"from\": 1456, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Certainly, Cyprus and Malta would have to leave the EU customs union.\", \"from\": 1828, \"to\": 1897, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other Commonwealth countries would also have to review their commitments to other countries with which they have joined in FTAs to ensure that the effect of Commonwealth preferences does not violate their existing agreements, which, in many cases, it must do to make the Commonwealth FTA beneficial to many of its participants.\", \"from\": 1899, \"to\": 2226, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Finally, the benefits of improved preferential access to all Commonwealth States within an FTA would be exploited by the major economies such as India, Malaysia and then by the developed Commonwealth countries, Britain, Australia and Canada.\", \"from\": 2228, \"to\": 2469, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Commonwealth's 36 small states would not get much of a look-in.\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Other options have to be explored by the Caribbean countries for dealing with the twin-problem of no formal trade relationship with Britain, and an existing EPA with the EU that is now skewered and ripe with problems.\", \"from\": 2539, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Caribbean has known for over a year that the referendum on 'Brexit' was coming.\", \"from\": 2758, \"to\": 2841, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The result could only have been one of two things - either Britain would stay within the EU in which case it would be business as usual, or Britain would leave.\", \"from\": 2842, \"to\": 3002, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the latter case, the scenario described above would be the reality with which the Caribbean would be faced.\", \"from\": 3003, \"to\": 3113, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Plans for dealing with it should, therefore, have already been thought through.\", \"from\": 3114, \"to\": 3193, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If not, the Caribbean has at most two years, and the clock is ticking.\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sir Ronald Sanders is Antigua and Barbuda's Ambassador to the United States and has served as Ambassador to the European Union, the World Trade Organisation and High Commissioner to the United Kingdom.\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Responses and previous commentaries: www.sirronaldsanders.com\", \"from\": 3469, \"to\": 3530, \"entities\": []}]}"